-- APPENDIX F  --  FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Q. How do I change the toggle keybind?
-- A. Three ways:
--      1. Pass ToggleUIKeybind = "K" when creating the window.
--      2. Call Aquafield:SetToggleKeybind("F") at any time.
--      3. Open the auto-injected Settings tab and click the
--         "Toggle UI" keybind picker, then press your new key.
--    The default is K.
--
-- Q. The UI vanished and the keybind no longer brings it back?
-- A. Either:
--      - The ScreenGui was destroyed by another script
--        (call Aquafield:Destroy() then re-create your window), or
--      - Another script captured the InputBegan event with
--        gameProcessed = true. Try a different key in Settings.
--
-- Q. Can I run two Aquafield windows at once?
-- A. Yes. Call CreateWindow twice. Both windows share the
--    single ScreenGui and the single toggle keybind, so pressing
--    K will hide / show both at the same time.
--
-- Q. The keybind picker doesn't update the toggle key?
-- A. It does, but with a 0.2s polling delay. If you need
--    instant updates, call Aquafield:SetToggleKeybind() yourself.
--
-- Q. Can I disable the auto-injected Settings tab?
-- A. Yes - comment out the `do ... Settings ... end` block
--    near the bottom of CreateWindow.
--
-- Q. Are notifications themed?
-- A. Yes. They use the current theme's Sidebar / Accent / Text
--    / SubText tokens, so they shift colors when SetTheme runs.
--
-- Q. Does it support touch screens?
-- A. Yes. Drag, sliders, color picker, and dropdowns all
--    listen for Enum.UserInputType.Touch alongside MouseButton1.
--
-- Q. Why is my config not saving?
-- A. The host executor must expose writefile / readfile / isfile.
--    Vanilla Roblox does not; this only works in script
--    executors that whitelist those globals.
--
-- Q. How do I add my own theme?
-- A. Add an entry to the Themes table at the top of this file.
--    All keys (Background, Sidebar, Topbar, Element,
--    ElementHover, Accent, AccentSoft, Text, SubText, Border,
--    Success, Error) are required.

